            "answer_text": "Will , I can definitely describe 2020 with two words. Let me tell you two words : Reality Nightmares. The pandemic made many people suffer badly not only the poor but also the rich people. The corona virus (CONVID-19 ) which started in September 2019 now struck the earth with chaos and panic which can cause death in the lungs. The rich may or may not be affected but the poor have to endure the most when the world's people is 36 percent living in extreme poverty and still continuously rising. Climate change is one thing , government problems are one thing and now the Corona Virus. It really hard to adapt for the poor , one mess is already difficult enough but at this rate the stakes are getting higher for the poor people. But let\u2019s not get our hopes down because the matters will only get worse. Food Donations and medical supplies are being donated not only the poor but also the countries. We must not look down on Chinese people because they are the one who aids countries with bountiful masks and beds. Countries helps each other. This is not the time to fail or give up but think of it as a test from god , the ability to withstand the virus , how can we survive ? how can we encounter with this disease and how can we fight this pandemic but do not let fear or death control you. Most importantly do not get your hope and dreams to vanish. One of my relative died not because of Convid-19 but with a heart attack. Even if it\u2019s not because of this pandemic I want you to know rich people can still suffer. Being one of rich people I can tell myself that I\u2019m one of the luckiest person among others because I have food to eat , water to drink and a shelter to stay comfortably in and being able to attend a school which many people can\u2019t get hold of these 3 things. My mom and grandma always tell me that do not waste water, electricity and money and to eat every single grain of rice from a plate and to cherish good memories with your loved ones because you will never know when they will go and perish from your life, however that moments I did not listen but now able to have all these things made me realize you are lucky if you have food, shelter and to properly attend a school. YOU MUST REALIZE TO BE GRATEFUL FOR WHAT YOU HAVE . There are many people below you who doesn\u2019t have these kinds of things . Not all the rich people will stay rich not will all the poor stay poor the whole life. That\u2019s called life. Life throws tantrums at you and yes that is called life. Once again, This is not a time to give up or fail , but think of it as a test from god, testing you ability to fight this disease, your choices. Think about how we can survive ? how can we encounter the virus? Do not get your hopes down but do not let death, fear and panic control what you are during this time. Most Importantly : \u201c WASH YOUR HANDS !\u201d (Thanks for reading !) :) ",
