            },
            "answer_text": "Disappointing ans upsetting. Disappointing as now we see daily, on a worldwide scale, how little people actually care about eachother and prioritize their own selfishness. Take for example, all these people refusing to wear masks just because they believe it's an infringement upon their freedom. Does it not ever occur to them that they could drastically impact the life of someone else? Does it not ever pass their mind that they could pass on a disease that could kill the loved grandparent of a close knit family? Just because it doesn't seem likely that they themselves will get sick, all they care about is their own selfish self. They will willingly sacrifice the lives of others just for the sake of their own \u201cfreedom\". Another selfish fact about these people; because of them, covid is more difficult to get under control. Borders are being closed thanks to these people, who not only flaunt not wearing masks or social distancing, but whom also trespass into other countries just to sightsee, while families and loved ones are separated from eachother, waiting, praying for the day that they get to be reunited. All those people \u201cpassing\" Canada to go into alaska just to sightsee, waving around the fact that they have found a \u201cloophole\" in the rules and regulations just makes it so much harder for people who actually care about others and following rules. It's so completely self centered and ignorant that for me personally, it's hard to wrap my mind around it. I'm an essential worker, working full time in a retail store. Right now, in Honolulu, we have a stay at home order till Friday as our cases have increased. What do we see here? Our store is packed. Really, no one besides the employees are distancing. People wear their masks so wrongly it's amazing how they're functioning as adults. And I'm sorry. But is a 30 pack of beer and lays potato chips really essential? Because of these people who flaunt their obvious disregard for rules, people like my friends and I (who are trying hard to stay safe) are being put at risk and punished for the bad behavior of others. When not working, I stay at home. I purchase groceries at work, go home, and stay put till the next day of work. I don't go to parties. I don't go out. I always wear a mask. I social distance myself further than recommended. And yet, I am being punished, again, for the bad behavior of others. I am one of millions who are separated by the closure of the borders from the one person I love more than anything in this world. I haven't seen him for months, and it's been the hardest thing, just because some selfish egotistical people don't care or think they're invincible. I apologise for the rant and long read; I'm actually really upset. ",
